Q: What is mailgun?
Mailgun gives you fully programmable email: send, receive, forward and store emails from your applications. 
Note that you should use your domain name the API URL and the API Key of the created mailgun account.
You have up to 200 mail per day for free.

From the command line or through an application you can:
* send emails (through their servers)
* manage subscription to a mailing list

Q: HTTPS Authentication?
username: api
password: <api-key>

Q: Testing with curl? 
Sending a message is successful if output from program is <Response [200]>
If reply is <Response [404]> something went wrong. Check the URL you are using. 

Q: How to format an STMP email?
Here you have placed a basic e-mail in message, using a triple quote, 
taking care to format the headers correctly. An e-mails requires a From, 
To, and Subject header, separated from the body of the e-mail with a blank line.
More @ http://www.tutorialspoint.com/python/python_sending_email.htm

